<div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 16px; border-radius: 8px;">
    <h4>Material 3 Carousel Features:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Edge Zone Shrinking:</strong> Items start shrinking when within 40px of carousel boundaries</li>
        <li><strong>Gradual Shrinking:</strong> Items progressively reduce in size (up to 30%) as they approach edges</li>
        <li><strong>Consistent Behavior:</strong> Same shrinking behavior whether scrolling left or right</li>
        <li><strong>Proper Border Rendering:</strong> Borders always stay within viewport boundaries</li>
        <li><strong>Material 3 Compliance:</strong> Maintains 56px minimum width per specification</li>
        <li><strong>Smooth Transitions:</strong> CSS transitions provide fluid width changes</li>
        <li><strong>Real-time Updates:</strong> Responds instantly to scrolling and container resizing</li>
        <li><strong>Overflow Protection:</strong> Hard overflow (items extending beyond boundaries) is handled separately</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Fixed Issue:</strong> Items now consistently shrink when positioned near carousel edges, ensuring the same partial visibility effect whether on initial load or after scrolling. The edge detection uses a 40px zone to start shrinking before items actually reach the boundaries.</p>
</div>

<button onclick="(() => {
let carousel = document.querySelector('.tnt-carousel-viewport');
carousel.scroll({top:0, left: carousel.scrollLeft + 1});
})()">
    scroll Right
</button>
<button onclick="(() => {
let carousel = document.querySelector('.tnt-carousel-viewport');
carousel.scroll({top:0, left: carousel.scrollLeft - 1});
})()">
    scroll Left
</button>